For the approve function, it has 2 arguments and the type of each argument is as follows: address, uint256.
- the allowance from caller to the first argument will be updated to the second argument.

For the payable fallback function.
- When the ether just received (i.e., msg.value) is not smaller than 0x2540be400:
  - the state variable lasttxblocknum will be updated to the current block's number.
  - When tokenprice is not 0:
    - the balance of caller will be updated to (the balance of caller+((the ether just received (i.e., msg.value)/tokenprice)*0x3b9aca00)).
    - the state variable totalsupply will be updated to (totalsupply+((the ether just received (i.e., msg.value)/tokenprice)*0x3b9aca00)).
    - When totalsupply is not 0:
      - the state variable redeemprice will be updated to ((((the balance of the address of this contract*0x3b9aca00)/totalsupply)*900)/1000).
      - the state variable tokenprice will be updated to ((((the balance of the address of this contract*0x3b9aca00)/totalsupply)*1100)/1000).

For the transferFrom function, it has 3 arguments and the type of each argument is as follows: address, address, uint256.
